Colombia May Imports Rise 54.9% to Record $4.9 Billion

-- B y   H e l e n   M u r p h y
-- 
2011-07-14T21:21:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-14/colombia-may-imports-rise-54-9-to-record-4-9-billion-1-.html
Colombia ’s imports rose 54.9 percent
in May from a year earlier, the government statistics  agency 
said.  Colombian imports surged to a record $4.9 billion in May,
up from $3.2 billion a year ago. Colombia’s trade surplus was
$12.7 million in May, the agency said.  The peso rose 0.5 percent to 1748.50 per dollar from
1757.80 yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helen Murphy in Bogota at 
 Hmurphy1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
